{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/blepharitis/diagnosis/assessment/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"23eadfb4-a45e-50b5-9d14-0f785ac86a84","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 100f2002-7a50-42bc-97c4-aa2b00ac4ef6 --><h2>How should I assess a person with suspected blepharitis?</h2><!-- end field 100f2002-7a50-42bc-97c4-aa2b00ac4ef6 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f209dd99-b6a4-46c7-ad92-aa2b00ac386d --><!-- begin field b1f40f94-d05e-48cb-901d-aa2b00ac4ef6 --><p><strong>Diagnosis of blepharitis is usually clinical.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Take a history asking about:</strong><ul><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/diagnosis/clinical-features/\">Symptoms</a> such as burning, itching and/or crusting of the eyelids.</li><li>Time of day when symptoms are worst.</li><li>Onset and duration.</li><li>Exacerbating factors (such as wind, make up, and contact lenses).</li><li>Previous treatments and response.</li><li>Comorbidities such as rosacea, seborrhoeic dermatitis and atopy.</li><li>Previous eye trauma or surgery.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Examine the person looking for:</strong><ul><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/diagnosis/clinical-features/\">Signs</a> of blepharitis such as red, inflamed, and crusted eyelid margins.</li><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/background-information/complications/\">Complications</a> of blepharitis such as chalazion/hordeolum, lash malposition, conjunctivitis and corneal defects.<ul><li>For more information, see the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/conjunctivitis-allergic/\">Conjunctivitis - allergic</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/conjunctivitis-infective/\">Conjunctivitis - infective</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/meibomian-cyst-chalazion/\">Meibomian cyst (chalazion)</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/red-eye/\">Red eye</a> and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/\">Styes (hordeola)</a>.</li></ul></li><li>Features suggestive of a serious ocular condition such as rapid onset of visual loss or an acutely painful red eye — same-day evaluation by ophthalmology is required.<ul><li>For more information, see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/red-eye/\">Red eye</a>.</li></ul></li><li>Associated conditions such as rosacea and seborrhoeic dermatitis.<ul><li>For more information, see the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/seborrhoeic-dermatitis/\">Seborrhoeic dermatitis</a> and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/rosacea/\">Rosacea - acne</a>.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Investigations</strong><ul><li>Investigations (such as swabs) are not routinely required but may be appropriate if blepharitis is recurrent with severe inflammation, the person is immunocompromised or does not respond to initial treatment.</li><li>Referral for biopsy may be indicated if an <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">alternative cause</a> (such as malignancy or autoimmune disease) is suspected.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field b1f40f94-d05e-48cb-901d-aa2b00ac4ef6 --><!-- end item f209dd99-b6a4-46c7-ad92-aa2b00ac386d -->","topic":{"id":"210e4b01-890a-5a0a-a3cf-efcece1eb08e","topicId":"1bba37b4-ec1b-49d5-acc1-6fc1671711cf","topicName":"Blepharitis","slug":"blepharitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in April 2019","chapters":[{"id":"b93c0a0c-4692-53c9-843f-49ee05545451","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9c38019b-31fa-5b39-9bb8-b27769998a9b","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9620e929-162c-539c-b063-b0d2d792fc78","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"fd79cb69-88c9-53b3-a6a8-4bc9d0b0848f","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"ccbb8929-8463-57af-b3d5-cf785a546c74","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"4111c3c7-ee03-523b-800b-280e6b45dfbf","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"aff6bd9c-9a5d-5a90-9983-0fb81983feba","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"ec8eea31-e7ad-50f8-a443-eb9120f2bd11","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"7d5547f8-0c93-5d41-9cd4-d98e71ef7975","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"4e0b92f2-dd2a-568f-9ce8-bfcc52e4599d","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"960b987f-d9f7-5a39-8b20-715ba8988e6b","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"250fbd5e-7fdf-5849-bf02-a9c794a764ef","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE Quality standards"}]},{"id":"44811d5c-7af7-54f4-8fbe-e23a28523234","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"09fc8800-1ae4-546d-be0b-62e044edfca1","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"6899ed96-f696-5938-9656-d097419cff77","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"9a08c813-358a-52ed-8317-6734ad0caa2c","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"9261cec2-b5d4-5c5d-9e32-4a0d9acc38cb","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"48fb1bb9-46aa-5515-a112-656b86a86a56","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"3916f955-e558-5e75-911e-ae48f8579e84","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"c59566b4-f12c-545c-8941-a7de38155871","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features"},{"id":"23eadfb4-a45e-50b5-9d14-0f785ac86a84","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"a1f19a88-0a61-5514-b729-f6ba8636d70e","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"aa038862-8424-552a-84d0-e962619a7e33","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"a41dab9c-d988-5d7a-813e-2d7a1658f5bc","slug":"management-of-blepharitis","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management of blepharitis"}]},{"id":"e0741730-0deb-5ab5-9f8a-0113b66dbe06","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"48e19546-bded-5436-9f23-e37a6fc78e36","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"b75f0439-fc4c-5236-954c-bfe59f6da9a5","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"b6a215d3-627d-577f-ba63-d0387c86ce0e","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"78dfcd62-db19-57fc-8f1f-0a100d3e4268","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"8e70896c-9149-59b5-b395-aa848fcd9ab2","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"4289ac7a-ea00-51b4-8b87-184e9a519291","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"28ab262f-aac6-5c78-badf-72aa21ca0119","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"3916f955-e558-5e75-911e-ae48f8579e84","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"0bece279-fd5a-5b8a-8a0d-f2ebfab33a6b","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-d0b","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 63c1b9ff-60c3-46de-820b-aa2b00ac4efb --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 63c1b9ff-60c3-46de-820b-aa2b00ac4efb -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d0bacfd6-fc63-4e97-ab40-aa2b00ac4efb --><!-- begin field 4c3a2a8d-750f-4118-ba9e-aa2b00ac4efb --><p>The recommendations on the assessment of a person with suspected blepharitis are based on the clinical guidelines <em>UK standards for microbiology investigations. Investigation of bacterial eye infections</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">PHE, 2017</a>], <em>Blepharitis – Preferred Practice Pattern 2018</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">American Academy of Ophthalmology, 2018</a>] and Blepharitis (lid margin disease) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">College of Optometrists, 2018</a>] and expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">Carlisle, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">Putnam, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>].</p><h4>Investigations</h4><ul><li>Public Health England (PHE) and the American Academy of Ophthalmology (AAO) guidance states that blepharitis is usually a clinical diagnosis — swabs are not routinely required but may be indicated if the person is immunocompromised, blepharitis is recurrent with severe inflammation or if treatment has failed.</li><li>PHE recommends careful interpretation of culture results as organisms commonly identified in blepharitis are often also isolated from the eyelids of normal healthy people.</li></ul><!-- end field 4c3a2a8d-750f-4118-ba9e-aa2b00ac4efb --><!-- end item d0bacfd6-fc63-4e97-ab40-aa2b00ac4efb -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}